io.elegie.luchess.web.client

Enum ClientContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ClientContext>
      • io.elegie.luchess.web.client.ClientContext
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ApplicationContext, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ClientContext>

    public enum ClientContext
extends java.lang.Enum<ClientContext>
implements ApplicationContext

    Our own application context, which make domain objects available to controllers (such as the services factory or the build monitor).

    The context should be initialized with configuration data, which can be retrieved from two external resources, which paths should be obtained from the configuration properties passed to the configure(Properties) method :
    • The Luchess webapp configuration file, so as to configure the execution flow of all requests. The key to be used is "luchess-web.configuration.file".
    • The Luchess engine configuration file, so as to configure all services. The key to be used is "luchess-app.configuration.file".

    Both configuration files must be located inside the classpath.
